    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - MAINTENANCE - HEATER ONLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="pm" graphiccount="1">
        <title>HEATER ONLY</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Control Cable Adjustment</title>
            <para>The heater cables on the Heater Only system are self adjusting (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1601409">Figure 9</hotlnk>). After the cables have been installed, rotate the control
                knobs through two complete cycles as follows:
            </para>
            <figure id="f1601409" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1601409" filename="../figg16/G1601409.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Control Cable Adjustment - Heater Only Models</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. BLACK FLAG-BLEND DOOR</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. CABLE CLIP</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. SCREW</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. WHITE FLAG-DEFROST DOOR</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Air Outlet Cable (Defrost)</title>
            <para>Rotate the air outlet selector knob from the DEFROST index line to the CAB index line and back to the
                DEFROST index line.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Temperature Control Cable</title>
            <para>Rotate the temperature control knob from cool (blue) to hot (red) and back to cool (blue).</para>
            <para>Repeat each step twice, check for complete sealing of the doors in each position.</para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
